Key Match Events: Goals from Jamal Musiala and Ilkay Gündogan gave Germany a comfortable 2-0 win over Hungary.
Dominik Szoboszlai (Hungary) is shown the yellow card in the 90'+3' minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Hosts Germany became the first team to reach the Euro 2024 knockout stage.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany had 69.5% possession compared to Hungary's 30.5%.
The match was held at MHPArena in Stuttgart, Germany, with an attendance of 54,000.
